    "shortDescription": "Every dolphin has its own signature whistle — a sound it makes that works like its personal name — and other dolphins use that whistle to call it specifically. They live in pods, and the relationships inside a pod can last a lifetime, with dolphins looking out for injured or sick companions for weeks. Fun fact: Dolphins sleep with only half their brain at a time — one half rests while the other stays awake so they keep breathing and swimming."
